      "id": "f2af6e64-eb69-4c6b-b053-6a9a8c79615c",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soient $f$ et $g$ deux fonctions continues par morceaux et positives sur $[0,1]$ telles que\n\n$\\forall x\\in[0,1],\\;f(x)g(x)\\geq1$. Montrer que $(\\int_{0}^{1}f(t)\\;dt)(\\int_{0}^{1}g(t)\\;dt)\\geq1$.",
        "html": "<p>Soient <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(g\\)</span> deux fonctions continues par morceaux et positives sur <span class=\"math inline\">\\([0,1]\\)</span> telles que</p>\n<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\forall x\\in[0,1],\\;f(x)g(x)\\geq1\\)</span>. Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\((\\int_{0}^{1}f(t)\\;dt)(\\int_{0}^{1}g(t)\\;dt)\\geq1\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "e174fa8f-ea63-4805-a8b8-40f7e2b5b673",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "D'après l'inégalité de \\textsc{Cauchy}-\\textsc{Schwarz},\n\n$$\\left(\\int_{0}^{1}f(t)\\;dt\\right)\\left(\\int_{0}^{1}g(t)\\;dt\\right)=\\left(\\int_{0}^{1}(\\sqrt{f(t)})^2\\;dt\\right)\\left(\\int_{0}^{1}(\\sqrt{g(t)})^2\\;dt\\right)\\geq\\left(\\int_{0}^{1}\\sqrt{f(t)}\\sqrt{g(t)}\\;dt\\right)^2\\geq\\left(\\int_{0}^{1}1\\;dt\\right)^2=1.$$",
        "html": "<p>D’après l’inégalité de <span class=\"smallcaps\">Cauchy</span>-<span class=\"smallcaps\">Schwarz</span>,</p>\n<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[\\left(\\int_{0}^{1}f(t)\\;dt\\right)\\left(\\int_{0}^{1}g(t)\\;dt\\right)=\\left(\\int_{0}^{1}(\\sqrt{f(t)})^2\\;dt\\right)\\left(\\int_{0}^{1}(\\sqrt{g(t)})^2\\;dt\\right)\\geq\\left(\\int_{0}^{1}\\sqrt{f(t)}\\sqrt{g(t)}\\;dt\\right)^2\\geq\\left(\\int_{0}^{1}1\\;dt\\right)^2=1.\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    }
  ]
